- Use Expo Router for file-based navigation with proper TypeScript support
- Implement deep linking for better user experience with booking URLs
- Use context or Zustand for global state management across navigators
- Keep navigation state in sync with the app state
- Use proper TypeScript types for navigation parameters
- Implement proper authentication flow with protected routes
- Use tab navigation for main app sections (Home, Search, Favorites, Profile)
- Implement proper back button handling and navigation history
- Use proper loading states during navigation transitions
- Implement proper error boundaries for navigation errors
- Use proper route guards for role-based access (Customer, Provider, Admin)
- Implement proper deep linking for booking confirmations and payment callbacks
- Use proper navigation animations and transitions
- Implement proper navigation state persistence
- Use proper navigation testing with Expo Router testing utilities